DENMARK: Although smoking is banned in hospitals, public transportation and shops, Danes can still have a puff in Copenhagen cafes and restaurants so long as they don't bother others.
BRAZIL: A recent ban on smoking in public buildings and on short flights is widely ignored.
BELGIUM: Belgian law bans or curbs smoking in public places, but enforcement is sloppy, violations rampant.
EGYPT: Smokers puff away almost anywhere: on buses, in elevators, next to ``No Smoking'' signs.
Iranian cabinet approved a bill prohibiting smoking in public places in a move to intensify its nationwide anti-smoking campaign.
